The paper focuses on image manipulation detection using deep learning-based models, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the limitations of handcrafted or predetermined features, indicating a need for machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of manipulation classification, which falls under the computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category.
